<item>
            <title>[DERBY-584] Mismatch between DatabaseMetaData and ResultSetMetaData for NUMERIC type</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-584</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Derby Reference Manual says that NUMERIC is a synonyn for DECIMAL. If you create a NUMERIC column, the Derby client DatabaseMetaData reports that the type is java.sql.NUMERIC. However, if you select from the table, the ResultSetMetaData reports that the type is java.sql.DECIMAL.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t really care what type we report. I just think we should be consistent.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
